title: [Lectures on surgery].
note_text: Binder's title; though lettered Volume 1, 1829, contents are complete.
reviewer_1_rationale: Title source (binder's title) + statement about content completeness statement

title: [Lectures on surgery].
note_text: The manuscript, written in ink on paper and bound in cloth with quarter leather, is not in Brodie's hand and does not correspond with his printed "Lectures" [1846 or 1852] or with his "Works" [1865]. It was purchased by Yale Med from Walford catalog 41 in April, 1962.
reviewer_1_rationale: Physical description (ink, paper, binding) leans 'object' + comparison of this work's attributes with  printed editions makes it 'worky'

title: Surgery and diary / Sewall Brown's.
note_text: Manuscript, written in brown ink on paper, was sent by Richard Wheatland to John Fulton in February, 1933. Dr. Fulton later donated it to the Yale Medical Historical Library. Entries include medical and accounting data.
reviewer_1_rationale: Physical (ink, paper), the content type (medical/accounting data), and provenance metadata on this metadata

title: Physiology : lectures on the physical conditions of the tissues of the human body as applied to the explanation of vital phenomena : delivered at the College of France, 1834 / by F. Magendie, Professor of Physiology and Medicine, 1834.
note_text: Manuscript, neatly written in English and bound in quarter leather, includes 24 lectures; it was purchased by Yale Med in 1958.

title: Receipes for takeing of cemicals, 1850.
note_text: Page 3 has small label pasted on, reading: "Salts of gold, Meade Brothers, Importers, No. 233 Broadway, N.Y." The brothers established that location in 1850, hence the dating of the document.
reviewer_1_rationale: The 'pasted label'is used as physical evidence used to establish date; combines object and dating rationale on the object

title: Note-book of experiments and observations on anatomy and physiology / George Gulliver, January 1839.
note_text: Manuscript notebook bound in quarter leather, written in black ink on unlined paper, kept by Gulliver over a period of years, the last one seeming to be 1874; titled from author's inscription inside front cover.
reviewer_1_rationale: The binding, ink, paper physical description + title source + temporal scope

title: Note-book of experiments and observations on anatomy and physiology / George Gulliver, January 1839.
note_text: Inserted are several letters addressed to the author from John Davy and one from Thomas Hodgkin; also an "Obituary notice" of Gulliver written in his own hand.
reviewer_1_rationale: The material description makes it 'object' (i.e. the physical stuff like blank pages, inserted leaves) but also the content (index)

title: Excelsior diary : Columbian edition, 1893 / [signed in ink on title page: Geo. W. Vansint].
note_text: Although this is obviously a physician's book, detailing his practice in New York City, I can find no listing of Vansint in Polk's, AMA, NUC, New York Acad., or Worldcat directories.
reviewer_1_rationale: Cataloger's research note about their failed attempt at IDing suggests 'admin', but perhaps 'object' may make sense too?
